    priceLevel: '$$$',
    notes: 'Alcohol not included.',
    description: 'Drake Bay Getaway Resort is a small family-run eco-lodge on the edge of Costa Rica\'s Osa Peninsula, one of the most biologically intense corners of the planet. The property leans into adventure rather than luxury, with simple cabins, hearty meals, and easy access to Corcovado National Park\'s wildlife. Note that alcohol is not included in the all-inclusive rate — guests pay separately at the bar.',
    heroTagline: 'Eco-adventure base camp on Costa Rica\'s wild Osa Peninsula.',
    whatYouNeedToKnow: 'Getting here is part of the experience: most guests fly into San Jose (SJO) and connect on a short domestic flight to Drake Bay, though a long overland drive plus boat transfer is possible. The all-inclusive covers meals, non-alcoholic drinks, and most on-site amenities, but alcohol is charged separately and many of the marquee tours (Corcovado, Cano Island) carry additional fees. The Osa is humid and rustic — expect mosquitoes, dirt roads, and patchy Wi-Fi. The Osa sits outside the Atlantic hurricane belt, so storm risk is minimal. Pack reef-safe sunscreen, quick-dry layers, and good walking shoes.',
